11-1 timing dropout solution
text: We think channel 15 of the STB in LI11 crate 3 is damaged, so we connected the LeCroy to channel 9 instead. Triggers arrive at the crate 3 PDU, The STB applies a time delay, then pass the trigger to the LeCroy 2323A gate/delay unit where another time delay is applied before getting sent to 11-1 (SSSB?) via the NIM output. We previously used STB channel 15 (the general purpose channel) which may have been damaged during a recent crate swap. We commandeered channel 9 (used for obsolete PICS) and programed the same delay we have for channel 15, and wired it to channel A of the Lecroy using a replacement lema cable. 11-2 has a similar timing scheme but it uses some unit other than a LeCroy.

title: CATER 155811, Kly Mod 20-6: determined DQ current needs to be raised slightly to get better regulation.
text: Noticed with DQ current around 9.4 amps at Gun station, DQ voltage is a little high. DQ voltage needs to be closer to HV set X 2. DQ voltage should be 34.2 KV with set point of 17.1 KV--DQ voltage reads 34.5 KV. By raising DQ current, can get DQ volts to match set X 2. This will produce better voltage regulation from modulator. It is also possible the DQing divider or divider cable connections need to be looked at for readback stability. This work should be done during next available POMM.

text: Nick requested that we initiate a Restart//Reboot of the SPEAR1 server at the next opportunity. If we lost SPEAR beam, but couldn't fill it right away (like, maybe half an hour), this might be a good time to do this. This probably wouldn't dump SPEAR beam, but it will hold off the injector for a while and could have other fall-out. This has much lower priority than the Bridge PLC reboot because it might take longer to contact the off-site people (Clemens W or Derek Baity (408-644-5971)) who do this, and it's not affecting the machine presently. Reason for request: A s/w patch has been applied that is supposed to fix the issues that are causing the server to stop working (this has happened about twice in the last 2 weeks); the patch won't become active until the next server reboot.
